#!/usr/bin/env bash
# codex-codecheck: Run comprehensive code quality validation with auto-fix
# Usage: .ai/bin/codex/codecheck [--fix] [--quick]
set -euo pipefail

SCRIPT_DIR="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" && pwd)"
REPO_ROOT="$(cd "$SCRIPT_DIR/../.." && pwd)"
FLAGS="${*:-}"

cd "$REPO_ROOT"

PROMPT=$(cat <<'PROMPT_EOF'
Run a comprehensive code quality check on this project. Execute these steps:

## 1. TypeScript Validation (MUST PASS)
```bash
pnpm typecheck 2>&1
```
- Zero tolerance for type errors
- If errors found, analyze and fix them
- Re-run until clean

## 2. Linting
```bash
pnpm lint:fix 2>&1
```
- Auto-fix what can be fixed
- Report any remaining issues

## 3. Formatting
```bash
pnpm format:fix 2>&1
```
- Auto-fix formatting issues

## 4. Summary Report
After all checks, provide a summary:
- ✅/❌ TypeScript: X errors found (X fixed)
- ✅/❌ Lint: X issues (X auto-fixed)
- ✅/❌ Format: X issues (X auto-fixed)
- Overall: PASS/FAIL

If --fix was passed, automatically fix all fixable issues.
If --quick was passed, only run typecheck.

Flags passed: CODECHECK_FLAGS
PROMPT_EOF
)

# Replace placeholder with actual flags
PROMPT="${PROMPT//CODECHECK_FLAGS/$FLAGS}"

echo "🔍 Running codecheck..."
codex exec --full-auto -C "$REPO_ROOT" "$PROMPT"
